<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="283" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,677,1979]" pageId="2" pageNumber="283">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,281,677,703]" pageId="2" pageNumber="283">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Small-sized (length 
<quantity box="[533,712,677,703]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.075" metricValueMax="2.21" metricValueMin="1.94" pageId="2" pageNumber="283" unit="mm" value="2.075" valueMax="2.21" valueMin="1.94">1.94–2.21 mm</quantity>
), elongate orange species with yellowish to orange legs and antennae; pronotum 0.62–0.81 times width of combined maximum elytral width (
<figureCitation box="[1165,1238,716,742]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–2" captionStartId="1.[151,269,1961,1985]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,1056,1947]" captionTargetId="figure-244@1.[151,1436,1056,1951]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–2. Male habitus of Hydraena spp. 1. Hydraena rosannae sp. nov. (paratype, Sardinia, Villacidro, Cannisoni River). 2. Hydraena tyrrhena Binaghi (Sardinia, Aratu River, near Desulo). Scale bar: 1 mm." pageId="2" pageNumber="283">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). Similar to the widespread Sardinian 
<taxonomicName authority="Binaghi, 1961" authorityName="Binaghi" authorityYear="1961" box="[417,733,754,780]" class="Insecta" family="Hydraenidae" genus="Hydraena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="283" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tyrrhena">
<emphasis box="[417,556,754,779]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="283">H. tyrrhena</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Binaghi, G." box="[564,733,754,780]" pageId="2" pageNumber="283" pagination="66 - 77" refId="ref4505" refString="Binaghi, G. (1961) Materiali per lo studio della Hydraena italiane. Le Hydraena dell'Isola d'Elba e notizie sulla coleotterofauna acquatica associata (4 ° Contributo). Bollettino della Societa Entomologica Italiana, 91, 66 - 77." type="journal article" year="1961">Binaghi, 1961</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and to the Corsican 
<taxonomicName authority="Rey, 1884" authorityName="Rey" authorityYear="1884" box="[983,1286,754,780]" class="Insecta" family="Hydraenidae" genus="Hydraena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="283" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="evanescens">
<emphasis box="[983,1154,754,779]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="283">H. evanescens</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Rey, C." box="[1162,1286,754,780]" pageId="2" pageNumber="283" pagination="266 - 271" refId="ref5605" refString="Rey, C. (1884) Notices sur les Palpicornes et diagnoses d'especes nouvelles ou peu connues. Revue d'Entomologie, 3, 266 - 271." type="journal article" year="1884">Rey, 1884</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, recently redescribed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Audisio, P. &amp; De Biase, A." box="[316,680,793,819]" pageId="2" pageNumber="283" pagination="163 - 189" refId="ref4322" refString="Audisio, P. &amp; De Biase, A. (1995) Materiali per un'analisi biogeografica delle specie italiane dei generi Hydraena Kugelann ed Haenydra Rey (Coleoptera, Hydraenidae). Fragmenta Entomologica, 27, 163 - 189." type="journal article" year="1995">Audisio and De Biase (1995)</bibRefCitation>
, but with a much less deep emargination on dorsal profile of aedeagus (in lateral view), slightly more inflated apical portion of male hind tibiae, and slightly sinuose and dilated middle portion of male front tibiae (
<figureCitation box="[660,729,870,896]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–2" captionStartId="1.[151,269,1961,1985]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,1056,1947]" captionTargetId="figure-244@1.[151,1436,1056,1951]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–2. Male habitus of Hydraena spp. 1. Hydraena rosannae sp. nov. (paratype, Sardinia, Villacidro, Cannisoni River). 2. Hydraena tyrrhena Binaghi (Sardinia, Aratu River, near Desulo). Scale bar: 1 mm." pageId="2" pageNumber="283">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
